question.title: Getting error while opening login page in the chrome browser in the Intellij
question.body:
I am new to selenium using java concept and I am executing the login page using java language. I have downloaded Intellij and in this downloaded the latest stable version of Selenium Grid from the Selenium dev website and also downloaded the stable version of Chrome from the Selenium dev website.

package sampleapp;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;

public class Hello {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.setProperty("webdriver.chrome.driver","C:\\Users\\singh\\Downloads\\chromedriver.exe");
        WebDriver driver=new ChromeDriver();
    }
}

The error coming is:

java: cannot access org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver bad class file: /C:/Users/singh/Downloads/selenium-server-4.27.0.jar!/org/openqa/selenium/WebDriver.class class file has wrong version 55.0, should be 52.0 Please remove or make sure it appears in the correct subdirectory of the classpath.
